  "prompt": "How many women are FDNY firefighters?",
  "response": "As of the latest available information up to October 2023, women make up approximately **10%** of the firefighters in the Fire Department of New York City (FDNY). This percentage translates to roughly **1,000 female firefighters** out of the department's total workforce of around 10,000 uniformed personnel, which includes both firefighters and paramedics.\n\nThe FDNY has been actively working to increase diversity and encourage more women to join the ranks through various recruitment initiatives, mentorship programs, and supportive workplace policies. While progress has been steady, women remain underrepresented in this field, reflecting broader trends in the firefighting profession nationwide.\n\nFor the most current and precise numbers, it's advisable to consult the FDNY's official reports or contact their public affairs office directly, as personnel numbers can fluctuate due to recruitment, retirements, and other factors.",
